    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-04-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-04-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="891"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d891">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 2491/144.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Minister for Foreign Affairs of Costa
                            Rica</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">San Jose</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-04-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 8, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I have the honor to advise your excellency that the arbitration convention with
                    Panama has received the approval of the President of the Republic, and will be
                    submitted in May to the constitutional congress. On this occasion I take
                    pleasure in renewing to your excellency and to the Government of the United
                    States the assurance of our profound gratitude for your friendly mediation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">R. Fernandez Guardia.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
